--- Mark Hineline wrote:

Many (all?) cruise control systems include a 12 v.
vacuum pump as part of the package. Any pick-your-part
junkyard will have hundreds of them.
 
-----------------------------------------------------------------
 
Most newer cruise systems use electric motors.

I doubt very much that anyone will find any electric
vacuum pump that will have anywhere the VOLUME of
vacuum needed for a booster.

The consumption is massive.

Mercedes uses big mechanical vacuum pumps that are
engine driven on the diesels.  
